text:
Twenty years ago, Nike and I became partners in running. Since 2003, Nike has played a crucial role in my career, providing inspiration and innovation. Together, we've brought these elements to every athlete in the world.

Monday was a special celebration as we unveiled the Eliud Kipchoge Track at the Nike European Headquarters in the Netherlands, while at the same time Nike revealed a statue of me at the headquarters in Beaverton.

Thank you Nike for the great partnership, together we run as one.

text:
Receiving the Princess of Asturias Award tonight fulfills me with honor, as it‚Äôs an acknowledgement for something that I‚Äôve believed in thoroughly throughout my career. To some, running is simply an act of physical movement. But ever since I started running as a young boy in Kapsabet, Kenya, I knew running meant something much greater than that. Running is not just physical movement. Running is a vehicle that has the power to unite us.

We can only achieve greatness if we fully believe that there is nothing holding us back. There are no limits, just what our mind tricks us to believe. So, I urge to you see the world this way. To see the world without limits and to see all that is possible. A running world is a happy world. A running world is a united world.

Muchas gracias.

text:
It was really good to be back in Vienna for the first time since 2019. I can say that my memories from the INEOS 1:59 Challenge are still fresh in my mind, what happened in 2019 feels like yesterday. Thank you INEOS and the Daily Mile for organizing several runs on the same course continuing the legacy of our world-changing event.

Lastly, I want to thank the city of Vienna for the warm welcome, I'm so proud to receive The Golden City Hall man from the mayor of Vienna.

Lastly, I want to thank the city of Vienna for the warm welcome, I'm so proud to receive The Golden City Hall man from the mayor of Vienna.

text: To be the first one winning the Berlin Marathon five times is something that I could only dream of when I started my career. We have so much history together whereby I cannot put into words the feeling I get when running these streets. Thank you to all the fans out on the course today. I heard all of your cheers. You motivate me to keep pushing always. Berlin, my special place.

You cannot train alone and expect to run a fast time. I always say 100% of me is nothing compared to 1% of the whole team. That‚Äôs teamwork. That‚Äôs what I value.

Want to know what it takes to run a marathon and how we prepare as a team? Join the NN Running Team on September 22 at the Babylon Cinema in Berlin. My coach Patrick Sang alongside other NN Running Team key members will tell you everything about my preparation, trainings and more insides of my raceweek.
Find all the information on the event and to buy your tickets visit the link: https://www.eventbrite.nl/e/behind-the-team-tickets-682073639617?fbclid=PAAaah0u0rAJUi9DrI9EewMzqPz9vJGxFui1r897e1ugRQj0ypuWDWL05wSqU_aem_AeIxwIvSlj8u2tGT9vxeERXRGlq9kZBIz497f89xDO3tfXx1XIt64_tlmWArN_agHU0

text:
It's always a pleasure to have journalists from all around the globe with us in our Global Sports Camp in Kaptagat. Last week was a special week as 9 journalists from different media agencies joined us for a week to get a more in depth view on how we live, train and prepare for big races.

I can say media is crucial in sport as they expose our talents and achievements with the entire world. Thank you for coming all the way to Kenya to visit our camp and support us in the things we do.

text:
Today we celebrate the third anniversary of the INEOS 1:59 Challenge. I can say that I still see the legacy of this event everyday. Together, we‚Äôve inspired so many people in the whole world that No Human Is Limited and in this world there will be no more impossibilities. Today we celebrate the fact that you can break any barrier, there is no wall at all in this world.

I am still very great full for the entire team who helped us making history: the main sponsor INEOS, the world class pacemaking team, my NN Running Team team mates, the technical team, my coaches, and above all my family.

text:
Limits are there to be broken. By you and me together.

I can say that I am beyond happy today that the official world record is once again faster. Thank you to all the runners in the world that inspire me every day to push myself whereby I hope this result will inspire you to break your own limits. Whether that is your first run, a new personal best and anything in between. Believe that with the right heart and mind you can achieve greatness in all of life.

Berlin, I cannot express my gratitude enough. From the organization to the fans but also all the participants today who all won their own race today. To my family, NN Running Team teammates and staff, all my sponsors who support me endlessly and who all share in this achievement.

Thank you.

#NoHumanIsLimited

text:
I can say that BERLIN-MARATHON has great memories for me. I finished four times under the beautiful Brandenburger Tor, so this year will be my fifth time. In this video, I relive some of the great moments of the past years.

text:
Education is key for development and it also spurs growth and development in different spheres of life. I am really proud to have opened the Eliud Kipchoge library, where people through all walks of life can come together.

In this library, everyone can get knowledge in a personal and professional way. It will bring the community together, creating unity and sharing knowledge. Together we can create a bright future!
